==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Psyche
<hw>Psy"che</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<grk>PSychh`</grk> Psyche, fr. <grk>psychh`</grk> the soul.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Class Myth.)</fld> <def>A lovely maiden, daughter of a
king and mistress of Eros, or Cupid. She is regarded as the
personification of the soul.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The soul; the vital principle; the mind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <ety>[F. <ets>psych⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>A cheval
glass.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Psychian</ent>⟦br⟧
